metadata.description:
The term Large Super-Weapon Drones (LSDS), coined by John DeSouza - a former FBI "X-Files" agent who spent 25 years investigating counter-terrorism and paranormal cases - perfectly describes the sophisticated crafts appearing globally since November 2024. This assessment is supported by prominent researchers including Dr. Steven Greer, who warns these sightings represent advanced classified technology being deployed as part of a planned psychological operation.

Unlike traditional UFO/UAP terminology that obscures their true nature, "Large Super-weapon Drones" accurately identifies these objects as advanced weapons platforms. They display capabilities including instant acceleration, electromagnetic interference, and plasma formation - technologies developed through decades of classified research and reverse engineering.

These craft are appearing with increasing frequency over military installations and urban centers worldwide. Multiple intelligence sources suggest this represents the early phase of a coordinated operation that Werner Von Braun warned would culminate in a "staged alien invasion" scenario to justify unprecedented control measures.
This token serves as a decentralized platform for sophisticated investors and serious researchers to:

-Document and verify sightings
-Share real-time intelligence and analysis
-Build a community focused on understanding these events

This will be an organically grown project - no bundled transactions or artificial pumps. We're seeking long-term participants interested in uncovering truth rather than short-term gains. For those who recognize the significance of current events and want to be part of exposing what could be the most extensive psychological operation in history.

This is not for jeeters or those looking for a quick buck. As the community grows, the price and chart will take care of itself.  A small investment is all that is needed.

Please see website for more detailed information.

metadata.name: yesnoerror
metadata.description:
This is an experiment! yesnoerror is an AI agent that uses OpenAI's o1 model to find errors in published research papers. The AI agent uses it's $YNE coin to fund it's AI review system. The agent is starting with enough to run for 2 days.

In October of 2024 a research paper claimed that black cooking utensils were extremely poisonous. People panicked. It turns out there was an error in the paper and it was wrong. When the paper was given to the AI model o1 from OpenAI, it was able to spot the error. What other errors might be hidden in the tens of millions of published research papers? What mistakes have gone unnoticed? What if an AI went and found all the erorrs?
